ading for IT security managers, chief security officers, chief information officers and chief executive officers. It will also be of use to personnel in non-IT roles, in an effort to make this unwieldy subject more comprehensible to those who, in a worst-case scenario, will be on the receiving end of requests for six- or seven-figure excess budgets to cope with severe incidents. About the author Michael Krausz studied physics, computer science and law at the Vienna University of Technology, Vienna University and Webster University. Over the last 20 years he has become an accomplished professional investigator, IT expert and ISO 27001 auditor, investigating over a hundred cases of information security breaches. He has delivered over 5,000 hours of professional and academic training, and has provided consulting or investigation services in 21 countries. Buy this book today and better understand how to manage information security breaches in your organisation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aComputer crimes. 0aComputer security. 0aElectronic information resourcesxAccess control. 7aCOMPUTERS / Security / General.2bisacsh  aISMS.  aISO 27001.  aISO 27001:2013.  acyber breaches.  acyber security.  ainformation security breaches.  ainformation security management system.  ainformation security.  aiso27001.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSciendo All Ebooks Trial Collection 2024z97831115024960 cEPUBz978184928597140uhttps://sciendo.com/book/9781849285964  a978-3-11-150249-6  Sciendo All Ebooks Trial Collection 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles